 127:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c **** 
 128:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 129:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     For specific callback RxEventCallback, use dedicated registration/reset functions:
 130:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     respectively HAL_UART_RegisterRxEventCallback() , HAL_UART_UnRegisterRxEventCallback().
 131:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c **** 
 132:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 133:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     By default, after the HAL_UART_Init() and when the state is HAL_UART_STATE_RESET
 134:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 135:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     examples HAL_UART_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_UART_RxHalfCpltCallback().
 136:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
 137:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_UART_Init()
 138:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     and HAL_UART_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 139:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_UART_Init() and HAL_UART_DeInit()
 140:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 141:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c **** 
 142:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 143:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_UART_STATE_READY state only.
 144:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 145:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     in HAL_UART_STATE_READY or HAL_UART_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
 146:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 147:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccTOf7oE.s 			page 4


 148:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     using HAL_UART_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_UART_DeInit()
 149:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****     or HAL_UART_Init() function.
