 251:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****       (+) For the asynchronous mode the parameters below can be configured:
 252:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Baud Rate
 253:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Word Length
 254:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Stop Bit
 255:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Parity: If the parity is enabled, then the MSB bit of the data written
 256:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****              in the data register is transmitted but is changed by the parity bit.
 257:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Hardware flow control
 258:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Receiver/transmitter modes
 259:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Over Sampling Method
 260:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) One-Bit Sampling Method
 261:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****       (+) For the asynchronous mode, the following advanced features can be configured as well:
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccTOf7oE.s 			page 6


 262:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) TX and/or RX pin level inversion
 263:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) data logical level inversion
 264:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) RX and TX pins swap
 265:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) RX overrun detection disabling
 266:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) DMA disabling on RX error
 267:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) MSB first on communication line
 268:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) auto Baud rate detection
